 Most Recommended Discussion









 Launch expert - Windows 10










Accomplishments









If there is trial version of Office 2007, then you could login to Microsoft website and buy new product key. But if you want to use Microsoft Office , I suggest to buy Office 2010, which is newest one by today.
http://office.microsoft.com/en-us/buy/buy-office-2010-FX101843016.aspx



Be the first person to mark this helpful            









        Helpful
    




    Solved my problem (1)




    Reply







Abuse history













                        Answer
                    








A. User

        replied on
        
July 23, 2010









 
Office Trial:
 
http://store.microsoft.com/microsoft/office/category/2

If you have Office (Word, Excel, etc) preinstalled on your Computer/Laptop that you bought, it is a Trial version.
You have to buy Office, once the Trial runs out.
 
An Office Trial usually consists of so many days use, or you may use it “x” amount of times.

The Product Key on your Computer/Laptop is for the Vista Operating System, not the Office Applications.

You can buy Office from the above link, or your local Dept/Computer store.
 
Or, for a FREE set of Office Applications:
 
http://www.openoffice.org/


Cheers.
 

Mick Murphy - Microsoft Partner
        


